    {
      "title": "Subject pronouns (eu, tu, el…)",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Say who you are talking about — when it needs saying",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 1,
      "explanation": "Eu (I), tu (you, informal), el/ea (he/she), noi (we), voi (you all), ei/ele (they m/f), plus polite dumneavoastră. The verb ending names the person, so Romanian usually drops the pronoun — vorbesc românește — and uses it for emphasis.",
      "culture_note": "Politeness has tiers: dumneata (semi-formal) and dumneavoastră (formal, takes plural verbs). Start formal with strangers.",
      "references": [
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Romanian grammar",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romanian_grammar"
        },
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Pro-drop language",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pro-drop_language"
        }
      ],
      "drills": [
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} sunt din București.",
          "answer": "Eu",
          "translation": "I am from Bucharest.",
          "hint": "I",
          "display_order": 1,
          "cell": "eu"
        },
        {
