    {
      "title": "Gender and number — including the neuter",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Name people and things, one or many",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 2,
      "explanation": "Romanian kept Latin's THREE genders. The neuter is a shape-shifter: masculine in the singular, feminine in the plural (un scaun → două scaune). Plurals vary: -i (băiat → băieți), -e (casă → case), -uri (tren → trenuri) — learn each noun with its plural.",
      "culture_note": "The neuter covers most objects — a huge slice of everyday vocabulary follows the un…/două… pattern.",
      "references": [
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Romanian nouns",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romanian_nouns"
        },
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Grammatical gender",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammatical_gender"
        }
      ],
      "drills": [
        {
          "sentence": "Am două {{answer}}.",
          "answer": "cărți",
          "translation": "I have two books.",
          "hint": "book, plural",
          "display_order": 1,
          "cell": "feminine"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Am trei {{answer}}.",
          "answer": "surori",
          "translation": "I have three sisters.",
          "hint": "sister, plural",
          "display_order": 2,
          "cell": "feminine"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Am două {{answer}} în casă.",
          "answer": "pisici",
          "translation": "I have two cats in the house.",
          "hint": "cat, plural",
          "display_order": 3,
          "cell": "feminine"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Am două {{answer}} noi.",
          "answer": "scaune",
          "translation": "I have two new chairs.",
          "hint": "chair — neuter: două, not doi",
          "display_order": 4,
          "cell": "neuter"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Am doi {{answer}}.",
          "answer": "frați",
          "translation": "I have two brothers.",
          "hint": "brother, plural — doi for masculine",
          "display_order": 5,
          "cell": "masculine"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Cumpăr două {{answer}}.",
          "answer": "mere",
          "translation": "I am buying two apples.",
          "hint": "apple, plural — neuter",
          "display_order": 6,
          "cell": "neuter"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Doi {{answer}} cântă în parc.",
          "answer": "copii",
          "translation": "Two children are singing in the park.",
          "hint": "child, plural — masculine",
          "cell": "masculine",
          "display_order": 7
        }
      ],
      "paradigm": [
        "masculine",
        "feminine",
        "neuter"
      ]
    },
