    {
      "title": "The definite article is a suffix (-ul / -a)",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Point to a specific thing — the Romanian way",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 4,
      "explanation": "Romanian is the only Romance language that GLUES 'the' onto the end of the noun: scaun (chair) → scaunul (THE chair), casă → casa, carte → cartea. Masculine/neuter take -ul or -le, feminines swap -ă for -a. One word, article included.",
      "culture_note": "This suffixed article is a Balkan areal feature Romanian shares with Bulgarian and Albanian — not something it inherited from Latin.",
      "references": [
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Romanian nouns — definite article",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romanian_nouns"
        },
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Balkan sprachbund",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balkan_sprachbund"
        }
      ],
      "drills": [
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} este mare.",
          "answer": "Casa",
          "translation": "The house is big.",
          "hint": "house + the suffixed article",
          "display_order": 1,
          "cell": "-a"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} este nou.",
          "answer": "Scaunul",
          "translation": "The chair is new.",
          "hint": "chair + the suffixed article",
          "display_order": 2,
          "cell": "-ul"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} este interesantă.",
          "answer": "Cartea",
          "translation": "The book is interesting.",
          "hint": "book + the suffixed article",
          "display_order": 3,
          "cell": "-a"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} este caldă.",
          "answer": "Cafeaua",
          "translation": "The coffee is hot.",
          "hint": "coffee + the suffixed article",
          "display_order": 4,
          "cell": "-a"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} lucrează aici.",
          "answer": "Profesorul",
          "translation": "The teacher works here.",
          "hint": "teacher + the suffixed article",
          "display_order": 5,
          "cell": "-ul"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} este deschisă.",
          "answer": "Ușa",
          "translation": "The door is open.",
          "hint": "door + the suffixed article",
          "display_order": 6,
          "cell": "-a"
        }
      ],
      "paradigm": [
        "-ul",
        "-a"
      ]
    },
    {
